At {{H<U+00F6>he|2558|AT}} the '''Kreuzjoch''' is is the highest peak in the [[Kitzb<U+00FC>hel Alps]] in the Austrian state of [[Tirol (Bundesland)|Tyrol]]. 

The Kreuzjoch also forms the southwestern end of the Kitzb<U+00FC>hel Alps. To the west it is bounded by the [[Ziller valley]], to the southeast by the [[Gerlos valley]]. The Kreuzjoch's neighbouring peak is the [[Torhelm]] ({{H<U+00F6>he|2494}}).

